description_as_pub: Externally defined table of codes specifying a present on admission indicator for a particular diagnosis. US reimbursement formulas for some states and Medicare have mandated that each diagnosis code be flagged as to whether it was present on admission or not.  In the US, may be used in the UB form locator 67, Present on Admission (POA) Indicator.  The UB-04 Data Specifications Manual with the codes is available by subscription from NUBC at http://www.nubc.org/become.html
